<section id="command-modulo">
    <title>MODULO</title>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>MODULO</command> <parameter>dividend</parameter> <parameter>divisor</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the remainder of dividing <parameter>dividend</parameter> divided by <parameter>divisor</parameter>.
Both <parameter>dividend</parameter> and <parameter>divisor</parameter> must be integers.
The result is an integer with the same sign as <parameter>divisor</parameter> (unlike <link linkend="command-remainder">REMAINDER</link>, which uses the sign of <parameter>dividend</parameter>).
</para>

<para>
It is an error to call MODULO with a <parameter>divisor</parameter> of 0.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>SHOW MODULO 6 4</userinput>
2</programlisting>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW MODULO 6 2</userinput>
0</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
